\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def surfaceArea(self, grid: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        ans = 0\n        for i, row in enumerate(grid):\n            for j, v in enumerate(row):\n                if v:\n                    ans += 2 + v * 4\n                    if i:\n                        ans -= min(v, grid[i - 1][j]) * 2\n                    if j:\n                        ans -= min(v, grid[i][j - 1]) * 2\n        return ans\n```\n\nThis solution calculates the total surface area of the 3D shapes formed by the cubes in the grid. It iterates through each cell, adding the surface area of the cubes in that cell and then subtracting the areas of the faces that are glued to adjacent cubes.", "estimated_date": 1535241600000}